org.opensextant.extractors.xtax

Class TaxonMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opensextant.extraction.SolrMatcherSupport
      • org.opensextant.extractors.xtax.TaxonMatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Extractor

    public class TaxonMatcher
extends SolrMatcherSupport
implements Extractor
    TaxonMatcher uses SolrTextTagger to tag mentions of phrases in documents. The phrases can be from simple word lists or they can connect to a taxonomy of sorts -- the "taxcat" solr core (see Xponents/solr/taxcat and Xponents/XTax for implementation) JVM arg to use is "opensextant.solr" to point to the local path Less tested: solr.solr.home might conflict with a Solr document server instead of this tagger. solr.url is good for RESTful integration, but not recommended
    Author:
    Marc Ubaldino - ubaldino@mitre.org

      • extract

        public List<TextMatch> extract(TextInput input)
                        throws ExtractionException
        "tags" are instances of the matching text spans from your input buffer "matchingDocs" are records from the taxonomy catalog. They have all the metadata. tags' ids array are pointers into matchingDocs, by Solr record ID. // "tagsCount":10, "tags":[{ "ids":[35], "endOffset":40, "startOffset":38}, // { "ids":[750308, 2769912, 2770041, 10413973, 10417546], "endOffset":49, // "startOffset":41}, // ... // "matchingDocs":{"numFound":75, "start":0, "docs":[ // {records matching}]
        Specified by:
        extract in interface Extractor
        Parameters:
        input - text input
        Returns:
        the list of TextMatch
        Throws:
        ExtractionException - error if underlying extractor(s) fail
